@Node "What Is IR-Slave" "IR-SlaveE.guide/What Is IR-Slave"
@Next "Installation"
@Prev "Main"
@Toc "Main"

What Is IR-Slave
****************

   With the IR-Slave you can control your Amiga via any remote control!

   Therefore you can learn different infra-red signals of your remote
control (e.g. the remote control of your tv set) and assign different
commands/scripts to them.

   Then, whenever the IR-Slave hardware detects a infra red signal which
was been learned before, the assigned command/script will be executed.
You can for example show a picture when pressing the power key on a
remote control or start an arexx-script etc.

   The IR-Slave can also do its work hidden, because it is a commodity.
Up to 254 different commands can be learned.

   See @{"Hardware" Link "Hardware"}.


@EndNode

@Node "Installation" "IR-SlaveE.guide/Installation"
@Next "How To Use"
@Prev "What Is IR-Slave"
@Toc "Main"

Installation
************

   Requirements:

   @{b}*@{ub} Kickstart 2.04

   @{b}*@{ub} Workbench 2.1 or higher If you want to use the @{b}locale.library@{ub}

   Installation:

   The installation is very easy. No additional libraries are needed -
no assigns must be done.

   The only thing which should be noticed is that the IR-Slave should
be copied to a directory which is in the path of the workbench (e.g.
@{b}sys:utilities/@{ub}). Then the projects can be started from anywhere with a
doubleclick.

   For users of workbench 2.1 or higher:

   If you want to install the german catalog you have to copy
@{b}IR-Slave.catalog@{ub} to
@{b}Locale:catalogs/deutsch/@{ub} or to @{b}catalogs/deutsch/@{ub} in the same directory
of the IR-Slave.

   If you want to install the german catalog it Locale: you have to
type:

     1> cd IR-Slave_Registered:
     1> copy catalogs/deutsch/ir-slave.catalog to Locale:catalogs/deutsch/


@EndNode

